main event: Four different unidentified objects were observed on radar throughout the day near Tonopah Airport.
interesting points: The objects were detected in the same area and at similar altitudes on multiple occasions., The sightings occurred on 12 November 1958., Observations indicated that the objects were fairly stationary and appeared to be drifting slowly., A weather balloon was observed visually around the same time period., The analysis suggested the objects might be weather balloons due to their flight characteristics.
